  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Post-craniotomy emergence hypertension is a common phenomenon that may predispose to
      development of intracranial hematoma and cerebral edema.The aim of this study is to compare
      the safety and efficacy of Mgso4 versus lidocaine infusion for control of emergence
      hypertension after craniotomy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
